<number id="3DC224BFD116FFF4246FFF45ED610382" box="[561,576,229,255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
and a pair circular spots in middle of tergite 
<number id="3DC224BFD116FFF42204FF45EB4A0382" box="[1114,1131,229,255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
; yellow lateral margin on tergite 
<number id="3DC224BFD116FFF426B6FEACEFD6025B" box="[232,247,268,294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="2.0">2</number>
broader than in male (
<figureCitation id="13312A1DD116FFF4245EFEACED79025B" box="[512,600,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,358,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,351,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Oxycera signata Brunetti, morphological features. 18, male dorsal view; 19, female dorsal view; 20, male lateral view; 21, female lateral view; 22, male antenna; 23, male head, frontal view; 24, male head, frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191660/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC224BFD116FFF42469FEACED79025B" box="[567,600,268,294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
