<subSubSection id="C3106513D119FFFB2698FC49EDEF0669" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB53698D119FFFB2698FC49EDEF0669" blockId="8.[151,1437,923,1300]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AD119FFFB2698FC49EE1E077E" bold="true" box="[198,319,1001,1027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male of this species may be distinguished by dense hairs on the eyes, and a yellow pattern on thorax and abdomen. The female with a unique colour pattern on tergite 
<number id="3DC224BFD119FFFB2277FBB2EB190751" box="[1065,1080,1042,1068]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
is described here for the first time. R. Rozkosny (pers. comm., 
<date id="FFB41058D119FFFB2462FB98EDC5072F" box="[572,740,1080,1106]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="2009-05-25">
<number id="3DC224BFD119FFFB2462FB98ED7A072F" box="[572,603,1080,1106]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="25.0">25</number>
May 
<number id="3DC224BFD119FFFB24FAFB98EDC5072F" box="[676,740,1080,1106]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</date>
) compared the re-description of the male with the male 
<typeStatus id="54B1883AD119FFFB26C9FBFFEFDF0704" box="[151,254,1119,1145]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BD119FFFB2778FBFFED2B0704" authority="Brunetti" authorityName="Brunetti" box="[294,522,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Oxycera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signata">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AD119FFFB2778FBFFEE830705" box="[294,418,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">O. signata</emphasis>
Brunetti
</taxonomicName>
which is preserved in The Natural History Museum, London, and stated that the male specimen collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F31D7608D119FFFB2449FB26ED7E07DD" box="[535,607,1158,1184]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">China</collectingCountry>
is conspecific with the 
<typeStatus id="54B1883AD119FFFB25DCFB26ECCD07DD" box="[898,1004,1158,1184]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
originating from 
<collectingCountry id="F31D7608D119FFFB229BFB26EA2207DD" box="[1221,1283,1158,1184]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">India</collectingCountry>
without any doubts. The 
<typeStatus id="54B1883AD119FFFB276CFB0CEEBF07BB" box="[306,414,1196,1222]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
is labelled as follows: / 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BD119FFFB2499FB0CECB207B8" box="[711,915,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Oxycera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signata">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AD119FFFB2499FB0CECB207B8" box="[711,915,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">Oxycera signata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<number id="3DC224BFD119FFFB25C5FB0CEC9007BB" box="[923,945,1196,1222]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
Brun. 
<typeStatus id="54B1883AD119FFFB2256FB0CEB6507BB" box="[1032,1092,1196,1222]" pageId="8" pageNumber="27">Type</typeStatus>
